## Architecture — Nx Libraries by Type & Scope

```text
apps/                → application shells (retailer, admin, supplier)
libs/[domain]/       → a feature library — smart components + NGXS state/actions/services/models
  src/lib/
    components/      → smart (container) + dumb (presentational) components
    store/
      state/         → one @State class per feature (extends EntityListState<T> where it fits)
      actions/       → action classes, type '[Feature] ActionName'
    services/        → domain services (extend BaseHttpService, URI InjectionToken)
    resolvers/       → functional inject() resolvers
    models/          → *.model.ts (DTOs) + *.entity.ts (rich domain entities)
    config/          → URI InjectionToken + feature config
    [domain].routes.ts → lazy route with provideStates([...])
libs/components/     → shared presentational UI (type:ui, scope:shared)
libs/common, core/   → framework-light utilities, base classes, tokens (type:util, scope:shared)
```

### Tags & Boundary Rules (ENFORCED by `@nx/enforce-module-boundaries`)

- **Every library is tagged** in `project.json` with exactly one `type:` tag (`app` | `feature` | `ui` | `data-access` | `util`) and one `scope:` tag (`<domain>` | `shared`). An untagged lib escapes enforcement — treat it as a defect.
- **Dependency direction:** outer layers depend inward only. `ui` never depends on `data-access`; `util` depends on `util` only; `feature`/`app` may depend on `feature`, `ui`, `data-access`, `util`.
- **Domain isolation:** each `scope:<domain>` depends only on itself and `scope:shared` — **never** another domain's internals. Cross-domain access goes through a `scope:shared` lib.
- **Adding a feature `foo`:** generator writes a tagged `project.json` → add the `@supy/foo` alias to `tsconfig.base.json` → append the scope constraint to `eslint.config.mjs`.

## Component Rules

- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` on **every** component — no exceptions.
- Inject with `inject()` into a `#private` field — never constructor injection: `readonly #store = inject(Store);`.
- New inputs/outputs use signals: `input()`, `input.required()`, `output()` — never `@Input()` / `@Output()`.
- Consume NGXS state via `store.selectSignal(...)` — never the `@Select()` decorator.
- Tear down subscriptions with `takeUntilDestroyed()` (preferred) or the `Destroyable` base class.
- **Split smart from dumb.** Smart (container) injects `Store`, dispatches, selects. Dumb (presentational) has signal I/O only, zero injected domain state.

## State Rules (NGXS)

- **Never mutate state directly.** Deep updates use Immer `produce()`; shallow updates use `ctx.patchState()`. Direct mutation silently breaks OnPush and selectors.
- One `@State` class per feature, extending `EntityListState<T>` where it fits. State model and all model/DTO properties are `readonly`.
- List-loading actions use `{ cancelUncompleted: true }` to drop superseded requests.
- Selectors are `static` methods decorated with `@Selector([TOKEN])`.
- Action type format `[Feature] ActionName`; one action class per operation; payload via a single `readonly` constructor parameter.

## Service Rules

- Domain services **extend `BaseHttpService`** and inject a **URI `InjectionToken`** — never a hardcoded URL string.
- `@Injectable({ providedIn: 'root' })` for singletons. Return typed `Observable<IQueryResponse<T>>` / `Observable<T>` — never `any`.

## Routing & Forms

- Feature routes lazy-load their state with `provideStates([...])` in route `providers` — never eagerly register a feature state at root.
- Guards/resolvers use functional `inject()` style inside `canMatch` / `resolve`.
- Forms are reactive and strongly typed via `FormBuilder`. Reusable inputs implement `ControlValueAccessor`. Guard submit on `form.invalid`; read values with `getRawValue()`.

## Import Conventions

- Always use `@supy/<lib>` aliases from `tsconfig.base.json` — never a relative path across a library boundary.
- Import order (auto-fixed by `simple-import-sort`): side-effect imports → third-party (`@angular/*`, `@ngxs/store`, …) → `@supy/*` scoped → relative (`./…`).

## Style Rules

- Use PrimeNG CSS design tokens (`--p-*`) for color, spacing, and radius. **No `::ng-deep`**, **no hardcoded hex colors**, **no raw `px` for spacing** — use token scales (`var(--p-spacing-md)`).
- `strict: true`. No `any` without a justification comment — prefer generics or `unknown` + narrowing.
- `verbatimModuleSyntax` on — use `import type` for type-only imports. Prefix unused params with `_`.
- Curly braces required on all control-flow blocks; templates use Angular control flow (`@if` / `@for`).
